1
00:01:15,780 --> 00:01:19,950
[Yi'ang]

2
00:02:56,510 --> 00:03:00,270
[Born with Luck]

3
00:03:00,370 --> 00:03:03,200
[Episode 24]

4
00:03:08,910 --> 00:03:11,110
I did swindle Zhou Rong out of 30 million

5
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,560
to pay my gambling debts.

6
00:03:15,470 --> 00:03:16,130
I'm guilty.

7
00:03:25,470 --> 00:03:26,130
That's all.

8
00:03:28,630 --> 00:03:29,360
You did more.

9
00:03:39,470 --> 00:03:40,960
My greed has led to

10
00:03:42,790 --> 00:03:45,120
a terribly negative impact on the society

11
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,640
and caused grave trouble

12
00:03:47,030 --> 00:03:48,360
for the police.

13
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,060
I'm guilty.

14
00:03:55,329 --> 00:03:56,460
Really, that's all.

15
00:04:00,550 --> 00:04:02,350
Why don't you give me a reminder?

16
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:06,580
Ye Jian.

17
00:04:13,910 --> 00:04:14,790
Well...

18
00:04:15,430 --> 00:04:17,310
I-I need one more reminder.

19
00:04:20,310 --> 00:04:21,269
Yesterday, before Lu Yibo

20
00:04:21,269 --> 00:04:22,800
went for the bianzhong deal,

21
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,490
he told Zhou Qi...

22
00:04:25,950 --> 00:04:26,950
Go find Lang Bowen

23
00:04:27,010 --> 00:04:28,210
and ask him to help me.

24
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,180
Just tell him

25
00:04:30,350 --> 00:04:31,390
I will definitely not tell anyone

26
00:04:31,390 --> 00:04:32,390
about what happened

27
00:04:32,390 --> 00:04:34,070
on the night Ye Jian died.

28
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:35,640
Ask him to please help me.

29
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,840
What exactly happened

30
00:04:38,870 --> 00:04:40,270
on the night Ye Jian died?

31
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:44,480
Fine.

32
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,940
I'll give you one last tip.

33
00:04:46,630 --> 00:04:48,120
How would I dare lie to you?

34
00:04:48,190 --> 00:04:49,650
Everything I said is true.

35
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,659
Where is Bowen?

36
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,120
He got drunk and left.

37
00:04:58,159 --> 00:04:59,510
If you don't believe me, I'll call him

38
00:04:59,510 --> 00:05:00,510
so you can ask him.

39
00:05:00,830 --> 00:05:01,560
Call him now!

40
00:05:03,310 --> 00:05:04,720
So Ye Jian called you?

41
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:12,680
Don't tell him, everybody.

42
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:15,750
Hurry! Catch him quickly!

43
00:05:15,810 --> 00:05:19,810
Hurry! Catch him quickly!

44
00:05:16,910 --> 00:05:21,200
[Lu Yibo]

45
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:23,560
Yes.

46
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:26,510
Ye used Yibo's phone

47
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:27,510
and

48
00:05:28,270 --> 00:05:29,070
gave me a call.

49
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,440
What did he want with you?

50
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,340
He just asked me about that watch.

51
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,860
I told him I had given it to Lu Yibo.

52
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:40,360
Then,

53
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,100
Ye asked me about

54
00:05:42,190 --> 00:05:43,830
what happened to Lu Zheng that day.

55
00:05:43,830 --> 00:05:44,480
Ye was my good friend,

56
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,659
so I told the truth.

57
00:05:46,430 --> 00:05:47,870
He then hung up the phone.

58
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:52,600
After that,

59
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,570
I got more and more worried.

60
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:55,560
So, I called

61
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:56,310
Zhou Rong.

62
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:58,150
You called Zhou Rong?

63
00:05:59,159 --> 00:06:00,120
That was because...

64
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,850
Did you also tell him the truth?

65
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,890
How would I dare to do so?

66
00:06:03,950 --> 00:06:04,800
I just told him

67
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,630
Ye found out what happened to Lu Zheng.

68
00:06:06,630 --> 00:06:07,430
When Zhou Rong

69
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:08,930
was on the phone,

70
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,300
were his emotion

71
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:11,240
and tone

72
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,120
the same as usual?

73
00:06:13,270 --> 00:06:14,950
At first, he was quite calm.

74
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,720
Then, as I brought up about Lu Zheng,

75
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:18,720
he went livid.

76
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,830
He started throwing and smashing stuff.

77
00:06:20,830 --> 00:06:21,560
Are you sure

78
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,160
you told him about the watch?

79
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:25,430
Yes.

80
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:27,610
Anything wrong?

81
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:28,650
It seems odd.

82
00:06:30,510 --> 00:06:31,830
Given Zhou Rong's

83
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:32,630
temperament,

84
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:34,580
if he knew

85
00:06:34,750 --> 00:06:36,870
that watch could be evidence,

86
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:39,150
would he have let Lu Yibo wear it

87
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:41,360
and walk around for such a long time?

88
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:49,540
I guess I probably told him about it.

89
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:52,190
I have a bad memory.

90
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:53,940
Your memory is never good.

91
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:56,720
See if this is the truth:

92
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,000
Zhou Rong actually ordered you

93
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,780
to retrieve the phone

94
00:06:59,830 --> 00:07:00,920
and kill those two people.

95
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:02,920
But you didn't plan to do any of that.

96
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,650
You were there for the deal.

97
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:05,600
I heard you meant

98
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,870
to take 5 million out of your own pocket

99
00:07:06,870 --> 00:07:08,240
to pay those guys and have them

100
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:10,440
leave Sanjiangkou as soon as possible.

101
00:07:10,510 --> 00:07:11,070
Why?

102
00:07:13,310 --> 00:07:14,360
It feels like

103
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,000
you were eager to get the phone back

104
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,530
and put this matter behind.

105
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:18,800
That phone wouldn't

106
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:19,860
cause you any harm.

107
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:21,620
Why did you want it?

108
00:07:23,270 --> 00:07:23,830
Were you worried

109
00:07:23,830 --> 00:07:26,360
-that if we got the phone...
-I killed Ye Jian.

110
00:07:38,070 --> 00:07:38,920
Now that your investigation

111
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:39,920
has gone this far,

112
00:07:41,159 --> 00:07:41,960
I might as well

113
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:44,000
tell the truth.

114
00:07:44,970 --> 00:07:47,460
[Lu Yibo]

115
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:02,880
Ye,

116
00:08:03,510 --> 00:08:05,650
this must be kept secret from Mr. Zhou.

117
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:07,830
Listen up!

118
00:08:09,190 --> 00:08:10,520
It's too noisy on your end.

119
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:11,980
Let's talk face-to-face.

120
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,130
Meet me in Binhe Park

121
00:08:14,830 --> 00:08:15,720
by the creek

122
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,720
we used to swim in.

123
00:08:16,750 --> 00:08:17,950
I'll be on the way now.

124
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:29,870
Where

125
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:31,320
is the car now?

126
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:33,990
In my garage.

127
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:40,270
Chief.

128
00:09:40,570 --> 00:09:41,970
We found biology traces.

129
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,640
Go back and get some rest.

130
00:09:43,910 --> 00:09:45,640
I'll wait here for the results.

131
00:09:50,310 --> 00:09:51,400
Why did Lang Bowen

132
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:52,510
kill a man

133
00:09:52,510 --> 00:09:53,710
in such a strange way?

134
00:09:54,550 --> 00:09:55,200
I did some analysis.

135
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:55,930
First of all,

136
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,240
Given his skills,

137
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,360
it must be hard for him to fight

138
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:59,360
and kill Ye alone.

139
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,600
Second,

140
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:02,790
they were childhood friends.

141
00:10:02,790 --> 00:10:04,080
With the means he choice,

142
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,740
he didn't have to confront Ye.

143
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:18,890
It's a sunny day.

144
00:10:20,630 --> 00:10:21,290
Time to eat!

145
00:10:56,980 --> 00:10:58,420
[Zhou Rong] [Hu Jianren] [Lang Bowen]

146
00:10:58,420 --> 00:11:00,240
[Li Penggai] [Lu Yibo] [Zhou Qi]

147
00:11:00,260 --> 00:11:02,810
[Zheng Yongbing] [Liu Bei]

148
00:11:02,810 --> 00:11:04,290
[Mao Hongwei] [Xia Tinggang]

149
00:11:04,310 --> 00:11:05,910
[A stone with "Yi'ang" written on it]

150
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:06,650
[Fenglinwan Hotel Pub]

151
00:11:06,650 --> 00:11:09,220
[Ye Jian] [Lu Zheng]

152
00:11:17,140 --> 00:11:18,940
Chief Zhang, the results are in.

153
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:20,410
It's Ye's blood.

154
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:23,950
Has the murder weapon been found?

155
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:24,720
Not yet.

156
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:26,320
According to the recovery team,

157
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:27,740
it was likely brought to the downstream
by the water,

158
00:11:27,740 --> 00:11:29,320
with slim chances of finding it.

159
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:30,120
But Dr. Chen

160
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:31,910
and the experts
from the Provincial Department

161
00:11:31,910 --> 00:11:33,360
all think Captain Ye died the way

162
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,620
Lang Bowen described.

163
00:11:34,670 --> 00:11:36,860
[Zhou Rong] [Hu Jianren] [Lang Bowen]

164
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,550
If Lang Bowen were not the murderer,

165
00:11:36,550 --> 00:11:38,200
He couldn't possibly know that.

166
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,270
Besides, in that SUV,

167
00:11:39,270 --> 00:11:40,080
only Lang Bowen's

168
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:41,390
and Lang Botu's fingerprints were found.

169
00:11:41,390 --> 00:11:43,120
So, the murderer is Lang Bowen.

170
00:11:49,150 --> 00:11:49,960
Lang Bowen

171
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:52,520
spoke of a cutting board.

172
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:56,060
It is no easy job to make such a thing.

173
00:11:58,010 --> 00:11:59,870
Suppose Lang Bowen killed Ye Jian

174
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,320
in the heat of passion

175
00:12:04,030 --> 00:12:05,030
like he said,

176
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,140
then how did he

177
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,530
get that cutting board?

178
00:12:12,330 --> 00:12:13,110
What's more,

179
00:12:13,790 --> 00:12:15,450
he had the guts to kill Ye Jian,

180
00:12:15,870 --> 00:12:17,150
yet he would rather

181
00:12:17,150 --> 00:12:18,000
pay 5 million

182
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:20,200
than go after those two street loafers.

183
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,400
Don't you find

184
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:23,250
this logic strange?

185
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,440
But now, all the testimonies

186
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:26,080
and the chain of evidence

187
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:27,200
point to no one but Lang Bowen

188
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,000
as the killer.

189
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:39,720
Li Qian.

190
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,510
Who is Yangyang?

191
00:12:42,270 --> 00:12:43,190
[I went to take a shower
and I remember this clearly]

192
00:12:43,190 --> 00:12:43,590
[I felt terrible in the shower,
and Yangyang came in to take care of me]

193
00:12:44,670 --> 00:12:45,400
Yangyang...

194
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,530
It's Lang Botu's nickname.

195
00:12:47,670 --> 00:12:48,270
Thank you.

196
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:51,600
"Yang..."

197
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:55,400
"Yangyang."

198
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:57,480
"Yi'ang."

199
00:12:58,710 --> 00:13:04,000
♪ Doubt ♪

200
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:06,350
[Yi'ang]

201
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:11,820
♪ Doubt ♪

202
00:13:06,790 --> 00:13:07,520
"Yi'ang..."

203
00:13:14,110 --> 00:13:28,750
♪ Doubt, doubt the doubt ♪

204
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:18,230
[Yang]

205
00:13:26,550 --> 00:13:27,270
"Yi'ang."

206
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:30,960
"Yi-ang."

207
00:13:31,510 --> 00:13:32,150
"Yang."

208
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:34,870
Ye Jian wrote my name

209
00:13:34,870 --> 00:13:35,630
on the stone not because

210
00:13:35,630 --> 00:13:37,360
he hoped I could solve the case.

211
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:38,600
It is pinyin.

212
00:13:38,870 --> 00:13:40,070
"Yi'ang."

213
00:13:40,790 --> 00:13:42,080
Read "Yi" and "Yang" fast,

214
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:43,340
and you'll get "Yang."

215
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:44,450
"Yangyang."

216
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:46,340
It refers to Lang Botu.

217
00:13:48,580 --> 00:13:50,200
Whether Lang Botu killed him or not,

218
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:50,890
the murderer

219
00:13:50,890 --> 00:13:52,550
was probably still at the scene.

220
00:13:52,550 --> 00:13:54,030
Ye Jian feared that the murderer

221
00:13:54,030 --> 00:13:55,360
might see him leave a clue,

222
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:56,200
so he used my name

223
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:58,340
as pinyin to give us a hint.

224
00:13:58,550 --> 00:13:59,960
"Yi'ang" and "Yang."

225
00:14:00,550 --> 00:14:01,280
"Yangyang."

226
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:02,900
It's Lang Botu.

227
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,000
His fingerprints

228
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,200
were found in the SUV.

229
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:08,790
He is highly suspicious.

230
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,240
Improbable, Chief Zhang.

231
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:12,030
As far as I know,

232
00:14:12,030 --> 00:14:12,790
this boy rarely engages

233
00:14:12,790 --> 00:14:13,630
himself in their business.

234
00:14:13,630 --> 00:14:14,690
How could it be him?

235
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:18,250
Call Lang Botu.

236
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:34,920
Hello.

237
00:14:38,870 --> 00:14:39,600
Yes, it's me.

238
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:42,890
I'm heading to the airport.

239
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:45,750
He's flying abroad

240
00:14:45,750 --> 00:14:46,630
at 2 p.m. today.

241
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:48,390
With his elder brother in detention,

242
00:14:48,390 --> 00:14:49,990
he's going abroad right now?

243
00:14:51,440 --> 00:14:52,440
It's no surprise.

244
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,240
Isn't he supposed to go abroad

245
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:55,510
for postgraduate studies?

246
00:14:55,510 --> 00:14:56,910
He received his acceptance letter
long time ago

247
00:14:56,910 --> 00:14:58,080
and got his visa done.

248
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:59,600
The program starts
on the 10th of next month.

249
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,440
Maybe he's going overseas
a few days earlier

250
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:02,300
to rent a place?

251
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:03,610
Stop him.

252
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:05,480
On what grounds?

253
00:15:05,630 --> 00:15:07,600
He is suspected of murdering Ye Jian.

254
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,000
Got it.

255
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:12,950
Shall we interrogate Lang Bowen again?

256
00:15:13,980 --> 00:15:15,240
Yes, make a call for it.

257
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:23,000
Hello.

258
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:25,900
Chief Zhang asks
to interrogate Lang Bowen now.

259
00:15:26,150 --> 00:15:26,750
Right now.

260
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:29,670
When?

261
00:15:32,620 --> 00:15:33,420
Is it serious?

262
00:15:35,170 --> 00:15:36,500
What did the doctor say?

263
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:40,440
Thank you.

264
00:15:41,790 --> 00:15:43,240
Lang Bowen has been sent
to the People's Hospital

265
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,080
due to intestinal obstruction.

266
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:45,390
How did that suddenly happen?

267
00:15:45,390 --> 00:15:46,390
He choked on food.

268
00:15:46,550 --> 00:15:47,910
The doctor said he's fine

269
00:15:47,910 --> 00:15:48,600
and prescribed anti-inflammatory medicine

270
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:49,480
and two bags of glucose.

271
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:50,550
Lang Bowen is on IVs now.

272
00:15:50,550 --> 00:15:50,910
What a coincidence.

273
00:15:50,910 --> 00:15:51,670
A great coincidence, isn't it?

274
00:15:51,670 --> 00:15:52,750
He pulled the same trick

275
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:54,000
in prison before.

276
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:56,320
He deliberately chocked on food
till intestinal obstruction happened.

277
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:57,030
Then he was sent to the infirmary,

278
00:15:57,030 --> 00:15:58,510
and cured by a tube of glycerin.

279
00:15:58,510 --> 00:16:00,910
He did it
only to chat with the nurses there.

280
00:16:04,520 --> 00:16:06,100
How long will the IVs take?

281
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:08,600
It takes 4 hours
to finish 2 bags of glucose.

282
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,400
Four hours...

283
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:10,760
Four hours...

284
00:16:11,270 --> 00:16:12,330
What time is it now?

285
00:16:14,790 --> 00:16:16,550
The process will end at about 2:00.

286
00:16:16,550 --> 00:16:17,150
That is...

287
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:19,700
when Lang Botu's flight take off.

288
00:16:22,380 --> 00:16:23,790
There is another situation.

289
00:16:23,790 --> 00:16:25,440
Lang Bowen has been inquiring

290
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:26,460
about today's weather

291
00:16:26,460 --> 00:16:27,460
since yesterday.

292
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:30,320
He was afraid
that the flight wouldn't take off.

293
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:31,910
There must be something wrong.

294
00:16:31,910 --> 00:16:32,910
What should we do?

295
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:33,550
After all,

296
00:16:33,550 --> 00:16:34,750
Lang Bowen is a patient now.

297
00:16:34,750 --> 00:16:35,750
Is it appropriate to get him back

298
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:37,010
f-for interrogation?

299
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:39,320
Two 500 ml bags of glucose take 4 hours

300
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:40,510
if infused slowly,

301
00:16:41,030 --> 00:16:42,430
and 3 if infused quickly.

302
00:16:43,150 --> 00:16:43,750
That could give us

303
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:44,880
a window of one hour.

304
00:17:04,980 --> 00:17:06,579
Why is the fluid level so low?

305
00:17:08,550 --> 00:17:09,410
What's with it?

306
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:11,619
This might cause an embolism.

307
00:17:12,030 --> 00:17:12,760
Don't move.

308
00:17:18,349 --> 00:17:19,680
What are you looking at?

309
00:17:20,550 --> 00:17:21,420
You perv.

310
00:17:21,510 --> 00:17:21,960
No.

311
00:17:22,910 --> 00:17:24,369
I'm looking at your watch.

312
00:17:25,310 --> 00:17:27,380
[Infusion Room]

313
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:29,080
[Please keep quiet]

314
00:17:36,510 --> 00:17:37,110
Thank you.

315
00:17:52,830 --> 00:17:53,760
He's over there.

316
00:17:54,180 --> 00:17:56,060
[Washroom]

317
00:17:56,440 --> 00:17:57,510
Have you noticed the airport police?

318
00:17:57,510 --> 00:17:58,060
Yes.

319
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:01,840
[First Class &amp; Business Class Only]

320
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:05,410
[First Class &amp; Business Class Only]

321
00:18:08,770 --> 00:18:10,910
[First Class &amp; Business Class Only]

322
00:18:12,070 --> 00:18:12,650
Hello.

323
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:13,590
We've notified the police station

324
00:18:13,590 --> 00:18:14,450
in the airport.

325
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:16,510
Okay, just a second.

326
00:18:16,510 --> 00:18:17,240
Let me check.

327
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:20,240
Please make it quick.

328
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:25,160
Three officers in total, right?

329
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:25,560
Right.

330
00:18:27,270 --> 00:18:28,350
Please go through security check.

331
00:18:28,350 --> 00:18:29,150
Okay. Thanks.

332
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:33,660
[Infusion Room]

333
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:36,690
Wait.

334
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:37,120
Nurse,

335
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:39,400
there's much liquid left.

336
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:39,800
Why...

337
00:18:40,030 --> 00:18:41,240
are you replacing it so soon?

338
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:43,370
Are you the nurse or am I the nurse here?

339
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:45,750
Please don't be mad.

340
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:48,200
I was looking at your watch just now.

341
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:55,240
How long will it take
to finish this bottle?

342
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:56,040
About an hour.

343
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:10,770
[Man]

344
00:19:52,510 --> 00:19:53,040
Officer.

345
00:19:53,350 --> 00:19:53,880
Officer!

346
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:55,980
What time is it now?

347
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,330
Two o'clock, right?

348
00:20:07,790 --> 00:20:09,820
Please have the nurse remove my IV.

349
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:11,640
I want to see Chief Zhang.

350
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,200
Good afternoon, ladies and gentlemen.

351
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:21,030
This is a pre-boarding announcement

352
00:20:21,030 --> 00:20:23,030
for Flight ML4420

353
00:20:23,030 --> 00:20:24,070
passengers.

354
00:20:24,110 --> 00:20:25,790
Please have your boarding pass

355
00:20:25,790 --> 00:20:27,460
and identification ready.

356
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:29,550
Regular boarding will begin

357
00:20:29,550 --> 00:20:31,400
in approximately 10 minutes.

358
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:37,610
Chief Zhang.

359
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,000
I lied.

360
00:20:40,830 --> 00:20:42,090
What did you lie about?

361
00:20:42,350 --> 00:20:43,680
I didn't kill Ye Jian.

362
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:51,260
You spoke clearly about the details.

363
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:52,700
Who else other than you
would have killed him?

364
00:20:52,700 --> 00:20:54,000
I don't know who did it,

365
00:20:54,070 --> 00:20:55,400
but it really wasn't me.

366
00:20:55,510 --> 00:20:56,670
T-The details...

367
00:20:56,830 --> 00:20:58,200
I made them all up.

368
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:00,560
W-Was I right about them?

369
00:21:00,680 --> 00:21:02,010
But I was just guessing.

370
00:21:02,030 --> 00:21:02,790
You...

371
00:21:02,790 --> 00:21:04,190
I can prove I'm innocent.

372
00:21:05,110 --> 00:21:06,070
From my home...

373
00:21:06,120 --> 00:21:07,440
You know where I live, right?

374
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:09,980
[Stick to the truth,
follow the law in handling cases]

375
00:21:08,310 --> 00:21:09,960
From my home to Binhe Park,

376
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:13,180
[Remain committed to strict, fair,
and civilized law enforcement]

377
00:21:10,070 --> 00:21:11,590
one has to pass through Jiefang Road,

378
00:21:11,590 --> 00:21:12,150
right?

379
00:21:12,750 --> 00:21:15,070
Then, leave Jiefang West Road
for the Second Ring Road.

380
00:21:15,070 --> 00:21:16,200
Exit from Xiangcheng Road.

381
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:17,550
After that, just go straight
to Binhe Park.

382
00:21:17,550 --> 00:21:17,960
Right?

383
00:21:19,590 --> 00:21:20,790
Do you remember this?

384
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:23,100
On the night Ye died, there was

385
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:24,400
a joint operation

386
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:26,330
against drunk driving in the city.

387
00:21:26,780 --> 00:21:28,310
The police set up checkpoints

388
00:21:28,310 --> 00:21:29,770
at all the intersections.

389
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:32,830
That night,

390
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:34,510
I was blotto.

391
00:21:35,350 --> 00:21:37,350
There's no way you'd have missed me.

392
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:40,720
We collected the fingerprints

393
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:41,440
of two people

394
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:42,390
on the SUV—

395
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:43,680
only two.

396
00:21:44,750 --> 00:21:45,680
One was from you;

397
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:47,890
another one was from Lang Botu.

398
00:21:48,270 --> 00:21:49,530
If you didn't kill him,

399
00:21:50,190 --> 00:21:51,990
would Lang Botu be the murderer?

400
00:21:55,110 --> 00:21:57,130
He's just a kid.

401
00:21:57,510 --> 00:21:58,480
There's no way he'd have

402
00:21:58,480 --> 00:21:59,540
the guts to do this.

403
00:22:00,030 --> 00:22:00,590
Besides,

404
00:22:00,830 --> 00:22:01,960
why would he kill Ye?

405
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:04,530
Why would he kill Ye?

406
00:22:09,110 --> 00:22:10,570
If you really suspect him,

407
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:13,240
just ask him to come over for an inquiry.

408
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:14,640
But I guess it's too late.

409
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:17,260
His flight has already taken off.

410
00:22:18,550 --> 00:22:19,350
Can we make it?

411
00:22:21,270 --> 00:22:21,900
Yes.

412
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:23,590
There are 20 minutes left
before it takes off.

413
00:22:23,590 --> 00:22:24,720
That's impossible.

414
00:22:25,550 --> 00:22:26,810
His flight left at 2 PM.

415
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:29,170
It's been airborne for 40 minutes.

416
00:22:30,110 --> 00:22:31,570
Of course we know you lied.

417
00:22:31,750 --> 00:22:33,080
I also know why you lied.

418
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:34,070
You were buying time

419
00:22:34,070 --> 00:22:36,000
to cover for your younger brother.

420
00:22:36,920 --> 00:22:37,640
I'm sorry.

421
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:39,350
We also lied.

422
00:22:39,070 --> 00:22:40,450
[13:40]

423
00:22:39,750 --> 00:22:40,960
It's 1:40 PM now.

424
00:22:43,990 --> 00:22:44,670
Copy that.

425
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:46,040
Lang Botu.

426
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:50,060
[Police]

427
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:50,590
You are suspected of killing Ye Jian.

428
00:22:50,590 --> 00:22:53,200
Please come with me
to the bureau for the investigation.

429
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:53,920
I am now

430
00:22:53,920 --> 00:22:55,310
arresting you for your suspicion

431
00:22:55,310 --> 00:22:56,640
of intentional murder.

432
00:22:57,750 --> 00:22:59,210
There are too many people.

433
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:00,410
Come with us.

434
00:23:01,510 --> 00:23:01,920
Go.

435
00:23:06,310 --> 00:23:07,040
Chief Zhang!

436
00:23:07,070 --> 00:23:07,800
Chief Zhang!

437
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:09,510
Chief Zhang, I... I lied again!

438
00:23:09,510 --> 00:23:10,070
Chief Zhang!

439
00:23:10,070 --> 00:23:10,830
I killed Ye Jian!

440
00:23:10,830 --> 00:23:11,920
I really killed him!

441
00:23:11,920 --> 00:23:13,640
There was a serious traffic jam
that night!

442
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:14,440
Once I was stuck in traffic,

443
00:23:14,440 --> 00:23:15,590
I just took the alleys

444
00:23:15,590 --> 00:23:16,950
and didn't get checked!

445
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:18,070
Zhang Yi'ang!

446
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:22,960
I lied again. Trust me.

447
00:23:23,240 --> 00:23:23,970
Chief Zhang.

448
00:23:24,030 --> 00:23:24,910
Chief Zhang!

449
00:23:52,480 --> 00:23:53,280
Ye Jian...

450
00:23:59,070 --> 00:24:00,440
I killed Mr. Ye.

451
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:07,920
Tell us more details.

452
00:24:11,480 --> 00:24:15,420
♪ Throw, throw, throw the handkerchief ♪

453
00:24:15,510 --> 00:24:17,880
♪ Secretly put it ♪

454
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:20,350
♪ Behind the kid ♪

455
00:24:18,840 --> 00:24:22,370
[Lu Yibo]

456
00:24:20,550 --> 00:24:24,200
♪ Everyone, don't tell him ♪

457
00:24:24,750 --> 00:24:27,120
♪ Hurry up and catch him ♪

458
00:24:27,350 --> 00:24:28,750
Bowen, you've got a call.

459
00:24:30,270 --> 00:24:30,790
Bowen!

460
00:24:33,030 --> 00:24:34,200
♪ Throw ♪

461
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:34,640
Hello?

462
00:24:35,030 --> 00:24:35,640
It's me!

463
00:24:36,270 --> 00:24:36,830
Ye Jian!

464
00:24:38,270 --> 00:24:39,000
Tell me

465
00:24:39,890 --> 00:24:41,710
where you were the night Chief Lu

466
00:24:42,510 --> 00:24:43,510
had his accident.

467
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:46,640
Ye is our friend. That's true.

468
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:47,870
But Ye is also a cop.

469
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,000
You broke the law.

470
00:24:49,050 --> 00:24:50,780
Do you think Ye would let you go?

471
00:24:51,270 --> 00:24:52,350
Did you have this watch

472
00:24:52,350 --> 00:24:53,350
on the day Lu Zheng died?

473
00:24:53,350 --> 00:24:54,750
Even though the police
know the watch is mine,

474
00:24:54,750 --> 00:24:55,920
they won't link Lu Zheng's case

475
00:24:55,920 --> 00:24:56,720
to us.

476
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:58,020
I hired a hitman half a year ago.

477
00:24:58,020 --> 00:24:58,830
Why did you kill him?

478
00:24:58,830 --> 00:24:59,510
Lu Zheng's death

479
00:24:59,510 --> 00:25:00,790
is a good thing for us.

480
00:25:00,790 --> 00:25:02,720
He was the Chief
of the Public Security Bureau!

481
00:25:02,720 --> 00:25:04,450
Ye Jian didn't notice it was me.

482
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:07,070
He said

483
00:25:07,070 --> 00:25:09,070
the CCTV caught my brother's watch.

484
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:11,550
At that time, I believed

485
00:25:11,550 --> 00:25:13,280
my brother had killed Lu Zheng.

486
00:25:14,350 --> 00:25:16,030
Let's meet and talk face to face.

487
00:25:16,030 --> 00:25:17,480
Let's meet by the small river
we used to swim in

488
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:18,610
when we were little.

489
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:20,560
I'll leave for it right away.

490
00:25:45,350 --> 00:25:47,000
What's that?

491
00:25:48,070 --> 00:25:49,510
I made it

492
00:25:49,510 --> 00:25:51,440
for the robot combat competition.

493
00:25:54,640 --> 00:25:56,100
I had never killed anyone.

494
00:25:57,830 --> 00:25:59,560
So I could only use this method.

495
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:17,920
Yangyang?

496
00:26:20,830 --> 00:26:22,200
Why is it you?

497
00:26:29,070 --> 00:26:30,860
How come it's you?

498
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:24,440
Two days ago, Zhou Rong asked my brother

499
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:25,700
to trade for the phone.

500
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:29,320
My brother didn't want to go.

501
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:35,140
Go

502
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:36,870
a little further later.

503
00:28:37,030 --> 00:28:38,000
Find a payphone

504
00:28:38,020 --> 00:28:39,150
and call the police.

505
00:28:39,550 --> 00:28:41,950
No matter what,
don't tell them who you are.

506
00:28:41,960 --> 00:28:42,880
Tell the police

507
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:44,070
about the phone deal.

508
00:28:44,070 --> 00:28:45,590
If the police catch those two first,

509
00:28:45,590 --> 00:28:46,480
we'll be safe.

510
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:48,000
Do you hear me?

511
00:28:49,680 --> 00:28:50,480
No way, Bowen.

512
00:28:51,920 --> 00:28:52,750
Why?

513
00:28:56,480 --> 00:28:57,510
I killed Ye Jian.

514
00:28:59,830 --> 00:29:00,820
What did you say?

515
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:02,400
I killed Ye Jian.

516
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:03,930
I drove and hit him to death.

517
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:07,640
Do you think I'll let you go

518
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:08,640
if you say this?

519
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:10,980
You killed someone. You're amazing.

520
00:29:17,640 --> 00:29:18,240
Yangyang.

521
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:22,000
Don't joke about this kind of thing.

522
00:29:27,960 --> 00:29:29,190
Why?

523
00:29:30,550 --> 00:29:32,170
I thought you killed Lu Zheng,

524
00:29:32,170 --> 00:29:33,970
and Jian had found out about you.

525
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:02,630
Which car did you drive to hit him?

526
00:30:02,630 --> 00:30:03,270
The SUV.

527
00:30:04,310 --> 00:30:04,980
Where's the car?

528
00:30:04,980 --> 00:30:06,060
In the parking lot.

529
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:07,210
Where did you hit him?

530
00:30:07,210 --> 00:30:07,920
By the river

531
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:08,880
we used to swim in.

532
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:09,810
What time was it?

533
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:10,590
11:30 PM.

534
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:11,480
Did anyone see you?

535
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:12,040
No.

536
00:30:12,070 --> 00:30:13,670
There were just the two of us.

537
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:26,530
Lili,

538
00:30:27,590 --> 00:30:29,200
book the earliest flight

539
00:30:29,200 --> 00:30:30,730
to Mankesid for my brother.

540
00:30:34,830 --> 00:30:35,590
Once we book the ticket,

541
00:30:35,590 --> 00:30:37,120
you'll leave immediately.

542
00:30:37,680 --> 00:30:38,680
If anyone asks,

543
00:30:39,110 --> 00:30:40,960
just say you want to go there early

544
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:43,000
for house rental and other procedures.

545
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:43,960
Bowen, I can't leave.

546
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:45,480
You're going to leave anyway.

547
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:46,790
You're just leaving early.

548
00:30:46,790 --> 00:30:47,720
I can't leave you alone

549
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:48,270
here.

550
00:30:48,350 --> 00:30:49,160
Why are you staying here?

551
00:30:49,160 --> 00:30:50,020
Waiting to die?

552
00:30:53,640 --> 00:30:54,550
If I leave, what about you?

553
00:30:54,550 --> 00:30:56,110
I'm going to trade for the phone.

554
00:30:56,110 --> 00:30:57,160
Once those two bastards take the money

555
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:58,110
and get out of Sanjiangkou,

556
00:30:58,110 --> 00:30:59,050
we'll be fine.

557
00:30:59,240 --> 00:31:00,030
What if they don't leave?

558
00:31:00,030 --> 00:31:04,490
-What if the police find out about this?
-Then I'll take the fall for killing him!

559
00:31:09,110 --> 00:31:09,590
No way.

560
00:31:10,830 --> 00:31:12,030
I must turn myself in.

561
00:31:13,440 --> 00:31:14,440
Turn yourself in?

562
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:22,070
Even if that happens,

563
00:31:22,070 --> 00:31:23,310
I'll be fine.

564
00:31:24,790 --> 00:31:26,720
I'll admit that I killed him first.

565
00:31:27,310 --> 00:31:28,240
When your plane takes off,

566
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:29,680
I'll change my statement.

567
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:31,170
I have solid evidence

568
00:31:31,270 --> 00:31:33,070
that it has nothing to do with me.

569
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:34,270
You'll be

570
00:31:34,270 --> 00:31:35,400
abroad then.

571
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:37,570
Even if they suspect you,

572
00:31:38,110 --> 00:31:39,110
it'll be too late.

573
00:31:42,830 --> 00:31:43,430
Yangyang.

574
00:31:45,030 --> 00:31:46,190
Our Lang family

575
00:31:46,550 --> 00:31:48,080
has accumulated the merits

576
00:31:48,200 --> 00:31:50,130
to have a college student like you.

577
00:31:51,310 --> 00:31:53,240
I can't let anything happen to you.

578
00:31:56,440 --> 00:31:57,480
I'm sorry, Bowen.

579
00:31:59,070 --> 00:31:59,900
I'm sorry.

580
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:00,600
It's okay.

581
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:12,880
You have a bright future.

582
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:14,800
Why did you

583
00:32:15,070 --> 00:32:16,530
get involved in this mess?

584
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:24,490
That's my brother.

585
00:32:25,680 --> 00:32:27,240
I can do anything for him.

586
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:30,720
When I was 9,

587
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:32,320
my parents had a car accident

588
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:33,920
and passed away.

589
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:34,480
He is

590
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:35,610
my only family left.

591
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:40,440
"Sticking together for survival" might be

592
00:32:40,440 --> 00:32:41,900
just an idiom for you guys.

593
00:32:42,790 --> 00:32:44,270
You can say it easily without thinking

594
00:32:44,270 --> 00:32:45,600
about its deep meaning.

595
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:54,460
But it's different for my brother and me.

596
00:33:00,830 --> 00:33:02,090
You won't understand.

597
00:33:04,400 --> 00:33:05,600
Taking others' lives

598
00:33:06,790 --> 00:33:08,990
to help you stick together for survival

599
00:33:11,110 --> 00:33:12,640
is what I can't understand.

600
00:33:17,790 --> 00:33:18,590
Take him away.

601
00:33:44,030 --> 00:33:44,760
Chief Zhang.

602
00:33:49,880 --> 00:33:51,160
Can I see my brother?

603
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:55,830
No.

604
00:34:03,670 --> 00:34:06,730
I killed... I killed Ye Jian!

605
00:34:07,510 --> 00:34:08,590
Chief Zhang!

606
00:34:08,840 --> 00:34:10,469
I want to see Chief Zhang!

607
00:34:10,550 --> 00:34:11,530
Chief Zhang!

608
00:34:11,590 --> 00:34:13,590
I killed Ye Jian! I...

609
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:17,130
Chief Zhang,

610
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:19,159
I killed Ye Jian. Really.

611
00:34:19,690 --> 00:34:21,510
It has nothing to do with Yangyang.

612
00:34:21,510 --> 00:34:22,730
Please let him go.

613
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:28,690
I'm begging you.

614
00:34:29,110 --> 00:34:29,800
Chief Zhang,

615
00:34:29,800 --> 00:34:30,440
please.

616
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:34,920
Stand up.

617
00:34:36,210 --> 00:34:38,409
You will see no one if you don't stand up.

618
00:34:49,070 --> 00:34:49,710
Yangyang!

619
00:34:50,590 --> 00:34:51,510
Yangyang!

620
00:34:52,360 --> 00:34:53,100
I'm here!

621
00:34:54,179 --> 00:34:55,400
I'm here!

622
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:01,730
Yangyang...

623
00:35:03,230 --> 00:35:04,090
-Let's go.
-Go.

624
00:35:14,260 --> 00:35:16,030
Sorry, Yangyang.

625
00:35:24,550 --> 00:35:25,990
I'm sorry.

626
00:35:33,630 --> 00:35:34,690
It's finally over.

627
00:35:41,030 --> 00:35:41,510
What?

628
00:35:42,360 --> 00:35:43,110
I'd like to thank you on behalf

629
00:35:43,110 --> 00:35:44,510
of everyone in the public security system

630
00:35:44,510 --> 00:35:45,440
of Sanjiangkou.

631
00:35:50,070 --> 00:35:50,930
What time is it?

632
00:35:51,690 --> 00:35:52,750
What time is it now?

633
00:35:54,510 --> 00:35:55,480
What's the matter?

634
00:35:55,480 --> 00:35:56,710
Take me to the hospital.

635
00:35:56,710 --> 00:35:57,600
I need an IV.

636
00:35:58,400 --> 00:35:58,930
Let's go.

637
00:36:00,150 --> 00:36:00,630
Be careful.

638
00:36:00,630 --> 00:36:01,160
I'm fine.

639
00:36:13,900 --> 00:36:16,730
[Two months later]

640
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:27,070
I almost forgot my shoes.

641
00:36:30,280 --> 00:36:30,760
Zhang.

642
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:32,510
Is it really appropriate for us

643
00:36:32,510 --> 00:36:33,510
to leave quietly?

644
00:36:33,550 --> 00:36:34,550
We came quietly,

645
00:36:35,190 --> 00:36:37,050
just like we're leaving quietly.

646
00:36:37,550 --> 00:36:38,840
Parting is always sad.

647
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,650
We can't leave quietly.

648
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:44,070
Yi'ang.

649
00:36:45,710 --> 00:36:47,450
Why didn't you tell us you were leaving?

650
00:36:47,450 --> 00:36:48,580
We know everything.

651
00:36:49,480 --> 00:36:50,410
What do you know?

652
00:36:50,710 --> 00:36:52,280
You're transferred back
to the provincial capital.

653
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:53,400
It hasn't been announced yet.

654
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:54,080
We know

655
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:55,190
an amazing detective like you

656
00:36:55,190 --> 00:36:56,920
can't stay in this small place.

657
00:36:57,150 --> 00:36:57,790
Yi'ang,

658
00:36:58,070 --> 00:36:58,760
Sanjiangkou

659
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:00,280
has been a lucky place for you.

660
00:37:00,280 --> 00:37:01,540
If you agree,

661
00:37:01,760 --> 00:37:03,620
I'll call Director Gao right away

662
00:37:03,630 --> 00:37:04,320
to ask for his permission.

663
00:37:04,320 --> 00:37:04,800
No need.

664
00:37:07,400 --> 00:37:07,920
Yi'ang,

665
00:37:09,110 --> 00:37:11,640
on behalf of all the colleagues
in the bureau,

666
00:37:12,800 --> 00:37:13,800
I want you to stay.

667
00:37:15,880 --> 00:37:18,150
I'm sincerely asking you to stay.

668
00:37:21,110 --> 00:37:21,880
Why does this scene

669
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:23,280
seem kind of familiar?

670
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:28,130
Looks like Chief Zhang can't leave again.

671
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:30,130
A land that doesn't belong to me

672
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:32,500
is always worth remembering.

673
00:37:33,150 --> 00:37:33,610
Well...

674
00:37:34,110 --> 00:37:35,710
You should know when to quit.

675
00:37:36,230 --> 00:37:37,690
W-What do you mean by this?

676
00:37:42,700 --> 00:37:43,990
[Building 2]

677
00:37:56,880 --> 00:37:58,020
Nothing hurts

678
00:37:58,110 --> 00:37:58,880
more than

679
00:37:58,880 --> 00:38:00,250
an untold story

680
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:01,520
hidden in your heart.

681
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:26,560
Congratulations...

682
00:38:30,150 --> 00:38:32,800
On your glorious return
to the Provincial Department.

683
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:34,540
It's not easy to work
in the Criminal Investigation Corps.

684
00:38:34,540 --> 00:38:35,590
Yes, yes.

685
00:38:34,620 --> 00:38:41,300
[Building 2]

686
00:38:38,070 --> 00:38:39,330
Since you're all here,

687
00:38:40,110 --> 00:38:41,840
let's officially say goodbye.

688
00:38:42,150 --> 00:38:43,950
During the days at Sanjiangkou,

689
00:38:45,360 --> 00:38:46,110
your support

690
00:38:46,110 --> 00:38:46,960
for me at work

691
00:38:48,880 --> 00:38:49,960
is something I will

692
00:38:50,840 --> 00:38:51,900
never ever forget.

693
00:38:56,670 --> 00:38:57,270
Comrades,

694
00:38:58,230 --> 00:38:59,490
see you again someday.

695
00:39:11,150 --> 00:39:11,750
Thank you.

696
00:39:12,030 --> 00:39:12,720
Take care.

697
00:39:17,840 --> 00:39:18,360
Li.

698
00:39:19,150 --> 00:39:19,680
Chief Qi.

699
00:39:20,380 --> 00:39:22,380
You're always welcome to come back.

700
00:39:22,510 --> 00:39:23,480
You are the best partner

701
00:39:23,480 --> 00:39:24,460
I've ever met.

702
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:27,460
Don't tell Li Qian.

703
00:39:34,070 --> 00:39:36,800
We couldn't have solved
these cases without you.

704
00:39:39,630 --> 00:39:40,360
I'm leaving.

705
00:39:41,960 --> 00:39:42,360
Bye.

706
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:42,880
Bye.

707
00:39:43,670 --> 00:39:44,330
Yi'ang.

708
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:47,080
In a moment like this,

709
00:39:47,230 --> 00:39:49,290
don't you want to recite a poem again?

710
00:39:57,590 --> 00:39:59,580
"If life deceives you,

711
00:40:00,920 --> 00:40:01,840
don't be sad

712
00:40:02,510 --> 00:40:03,570
and don't rush.

713
00:40:04,590 --> 00:40:06,430
Joyful days will surely come."

714
00:40:17,110 --> 00:40:18,250
Chief Qi,

715
00:40:18,440 --> 00:40:20,000
what did Chief Zhang tell you

716
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,530
that made you laugh so much?

717
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:23,800
It's a secret.

718
00:40:24,550 --> 00:40:26,840
How painful it is
to keep a secret to yourself?

719
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:27,760
What is Chief Zhang's new position

720
00:40:27,760 --> 00:40:28,630
back in the CI Corps?

721
00:40:28,630 --> 00:40:29,430
It's a secret.

722
00:40:38,680 --> 00:40:42,620
[Another two months later]

723
00:40:51,400 --> 00:40:52,510
[Logistics Service]

724
00:40:54,010 --> 00:40:55,680
[Logistics Service]

725
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:55,480
Zhang!

726
00:40:56,670 --> 00:40:58,460
[Logistics Service]

727
00:40:57,230 --> 00:40:57,830
Come on in.

728
00:40:57,960 --> 00:40:58,360
You...

729
00:40:59,320 --> 00:41:00,070
Well,

730
00:41:00,190 --> 00:41:02,600
the ink box of the printer.

731
00:41:08,150 --> 00:41:08,810
The ink box.

732
00:41:10,150 --> 00:41:10,670
Thank you.

733
00:41:10,670 --> 00:41:11,130
Come on.

734
00:41:11,840 --> 00:41:13,280
By the way, I brought you a box of tea.

735
00:41:12,780 --> 00:41:14,640
[Liu'an Melon Slices]

736
00:41:15,960 --> 00:41:17,160
You did it on purpose?

737
00:41:17,630 --> 00:41:18,290
Testing me?

738
00:41:19,820 --> 00:41:21,020
Liu'an melon slices.

739
00:41:23,110 --> 00:41:23,710
Thank you.

740
00:41:24,590 --> 00:41:25,520
You're not busy?

741
00:41:25,670 --> 00:41:26,870
Stay with me for a bit.

742
00:41:39,550 --> 00:41:40,920
We've been back
for almost two months, right?

743
00:41:40,920 --> 00:41:42,380
Two months and three days.

744
00:41:49,280 --> 00:41:50,710
Do you want to go back to the front line?

745
00:41:50,710 --> 00:41:51,320
Yes, sure.

746
00:41:52,190 --> 00:41:54,110
But one should build up strength
before making a move

747
00:41:54,110 --> 00:41:55,510
and not rush for rewards.

748
00:41:56,400 --> 00:41:57,480
We should also give young people like you

749
00:41:57,480 --> 00:41:58,190
more opportunities

750
00:41:58,190 --> 00:41:59,030
to grow well.

751
00:42:02,190 --> 00:42:03,190
How have you been?

752
00:42:03,480 --> 00:42:05,010
What cases have you solved?

753
00:42:05,440 --> 00:42:06,440
They're all small cases.

754
00:42:06,440 --> 00:42:07,190
No big ones.

755
00:42:09,110 --> 00:42:11,960
Someone who has solved big cases
is indeed different.

756
00:42:11,960 --> 00:42:12,800
Don't rush.

757
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:14,850
Wait patiently.

758
00:42:17,510 --> 00:42:19,370
Just like this drinking machine.

759
00:42:20,670 --> 00:42:21,880
The logistics center has one;

760
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:22,540
CID has one;

761
00:42:22,630 --> 00:42:23,880
the Director's office has one;

762
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:25,920
the Veteran Cadre Bureau also has one.

763
00:42:25,920 --> 00:42:27,120
It may look ordinary,

764
00:42:27,630 --> 00:42:28,960
but it never slacks off.

765
00:42:30,710 --> 00:42:31,630
Wherever it is,

766
00:42:32,320 --> 00:42:33,380
it will stand still

767
00:42:33,880 --> 00:42:35,210
and always be prepared.

768
00:42:36,110 --> 00:42:37,910
Maybe the position is ordinary,

769
00:42:37,920 --> 00:42:39,180
and the duty is normal,

770
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:41,480
but this is its mission.

771
00:42:40,880 --> 00:42:43,530
[Police]

772
00:42:42,550 --> 00:42:44,610
As long as the organization needs it,

773
00:42:45,030 --> 00:42:46,290
it can heat up quickly,

774
00:42:47,800 --> 00:42:49,010
giving light in its heart

775
00:42:49,010 --> 00:42:50,160
to the people,

776
00:42:51,590 --> 00:42:53,450
and offering the burning passion

777
00:42:53,760 --> 00:42:55,070
to the public security cause.
